<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<package xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/packaging/2012/06/nuspec.xsd">
    <metadata>
        <id>RM.DomainDrivenVerticalSlices.Template</id>
        <title>ASP.NET Core Domain Driven Vertical Slices</title>
        <version>10.7.0</version>
        <description>
            A comprehensive ASP.NET Core template implementing Domain-Driven Design (DDD) with Vertical Slice Architecture.
            
            Features include:
            • Two template styles: ddvs/ddvs-clean for Clean Architecture and ddvs-modular for an LLM-friendly modular monolith
            • .NET Aspire 13.2 integration for orchestrated development and observability
            • BaseEntity/BaseAuditableEntity with domain events and automatic audit tracking
            • EF Core interceptors for domain event dispatch and audit field population
            • Performance and exception logging pipeline behaviors
            • Choose between traditional MVC controllers or modern Minimal API endpoints
            • Testcontainers support for integration testing
            • Optional React 19 UI with Vite 6, Tailwind CSS v4, and dark mode
            
            Ideal for developers looking to adopt DDD principles with modern .NET tooling.
        </description>
        <authors>Reza Mashayekhi</authors>
        <language>en-US</language>
        <license type="expression">MIT</license>
        <projectUrl>https://github.com/RezaMashayekhi/DomainDrivenVerticalSlices.Template</projectUrl>
        <releaseNotes>
Version 10.7.0:

Security:
- Pinned vulnerable transitive NuGet packages in both template trees via Central Package Management
  (without these pins, newly generated projects fail to build because NuGet audit raises NU1902/NU1903
  on fresh restore and TreatWarningsAsErrors turns them into errors):
  MessagePack 2.5.192 -> 2.5.302 (GHSA-hv8m-jj95-wg3x),
  Microsoft.OpenApi 2.4.1 -> 2.7.5 (GHSA-v5pm-xwqc-g5wc),
  SQLitePCLRaw.lib.e_sqlite3 2.1.11 -> 3.50.3 (GHSA-2m69-gcr7-jv3q / CVE-2025-6965)
- React UI: resolved all 9 npm audit findings (2 critical, 2 high, 4 moderate, 1 low) via lockfile refresh:
  vitest 4.1.9 (GHSA-5xrq-8626-4rwp), vite 6.4.3 (GHSA-v6wh-96g9-6wx3, GHSA-fx2h-pf6j-xcff),
  ws 8.21.0 (GHSA-58qx-3vcg-4xpx, GHSA-96hv-2xvq-fx4p), react-router 6.30.4 (GHSA-2j2x-hqr9-3h42),
  js-yaml 4.3.0, brace-expansion 5.0.7, @babel/core 7.29.7

Dependencies:
- Updated all outdated NuGet packages to latest-in-major in both trees:
  EF Core / Microsoft.Extensions.* / AspNetCore.Mvc.Testing 10.0.7 -> 10.0.9,
  Http.Resilience + ServiceDiscovery 10.5.0 -> 10.7.0, Aspire 13.2.4 -> 13.4.6,
  OpenTelemetry 1.15.x -> 1.16.0 (Instrumentation.Runtime held at 1.15.1; no 1.16.0 published),
  Swashbuckle.AspNetCore 10.1.7 -> 10.2.3, Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk 18.5.1 -> 18.7.0,
  coverlet 10.0.0 -> 10.0.1, Testcontainers 4.11.0 -> 4.13.0
- Both trees build 0-warning and stay vulnerability-clean; all generated variants build and test green

Domain events (ddvs/ddvs-clean):
- Fixed Mediator.Publish to resolve handlers by the notification's runtime type; events raised via
  BaseEntity.AddDomainEvent were previously dropped silently by the interceptor dispatch
- DispatchDomainEventsInterceptor now dispatches after a successful save (SavedChanges) and honors
  the cancellation token
- CreateEntity1CommandHandler no longer publishes the event manually; events flow exactly once
  through the interceptor (migration: the handler no longer takes an IPublisher parameter)
- Added mediator unit tests and interceptor tests; integration-test factories keep the production
  interceptors attached

Logging (ddvs/ddvs-clean):
- LoggingBehaviour logs request/response payload properties at Debug level only (PII and log-volume
  safety); Information level keeps request name, outcome, and error details
- PerformanceBehaviour and UnhandledExceptionBehaviour no longer embed the full request object in
  Warning/Error messages - only the request name

Version 10.6.0:

Templates:
- Added ddvs-modular: an LLM-friendly modular monolith API template organized by business module and vertical slice
- Added ddvs-clean as an explicit compatibility short name for the existing Clean Architecture template
- Preserved ddvs as the backward-compatible Clean Architecture template short name

Modular architecture:
- Added a single-project Minimal API backend with Entity1 module sample
- Added direct Endpoint -> Validator -> Handler -> DbContext/Domain flow without mediator, generic repositories, or Unit of Work
- Added Result/Error/ProblemDetails mapping for expected business failures
- Added SQLite persistence with EF Core configuration kept inside the Entity1 module
- Added optional Aspire AppHost and ServiceDefaults via --UseAspire, default true

Testing and docs:
- Added generated unit, integration, and architecture tests for ddvs-modular

Version 10.5.0:

Security:
- Fixed three OpenTelemetry DoS vulnerabilities (GHSA-g94r-2vxg-569j / CVE-2026-40894,
  GHSA-q834-8qmm-v933 / CVE-2026-40182, GHSA-mr8r-92fq-pj8p / CVE-2026-40891):
  upgraded OpenTelemetry.Exporter.OpenTelemetryProtocol + Extensions.Hosting to 1.15.3;
  pinned transitive OpenTelemetry.Api to 1.15.3 via CentralPackageTransitivePinning
- Fixed two Vite dev-server vulnerabilities (GHSA-p9ff-h696-f583 / CVE-2026-39363,
  GHSA-4w7w-66w2-5vf9 / CVE-2026-39365) by upgrading Vite to 6.4.2
- Fixed PostCSS XSS vulnerability (GHSA-qx2v-qp2m-jg93) by upgrading PostCSS to 8.5.12

Dependencies:
- Upgraded EF Core 10.0.5 → 10.0.7
- Upgraded Aspire 13.2.0 → 13.2.4
- Upgraded Microsoft.Extensions.Http.Resilience + ServiceDiscovery 10.4.0 → 10.5.0
- Upgraded Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk 18.3.0 → 18.5.1
- Upgraded coverlet.collector + coverlet.msbuild 8.0.1 → 10.0.0

Build:
- Enabled NuGet Transitive Pinning for deterministic transitive dependency resolution

Version 10.4.0:

API Style Customization:
- Choose between traditional MVC controllers (--ApiType Controller, default) or modern Minimal API endpoints (--ApiType MinimalApi) when creating a project
- Both API styles use consistent /api/{Entity} routes
- Minimal API endpoints aligned with controller response patterns for integration test compatibility

Security:
- Fixed minimatch ReDoS vulnerability (CVE-2026-27903) in React UI dependencies
- Updated transitive dependencies (ajv, flatted, rollup) to resolve additional vulnerabilities

Version 10.3.0:

.NET Aspire Integration:
- Added Aspire 13.1 AppHost for orchestrated application startup
- Added ServiceDefaults with OpenTelemetry, health checks, service discovery, and resilience
- React UI automatically integrated via AddViteApp() when UiType=React

Domain &amp; Infrastructure:
- Added BaseEntity with domain event collection
- Added BaseAuditableEntity with automatic audit fields (CreatedAt/By, ModifiedAt/By)
- Added AuditableEntityInterceptor for automatic audit field population
- Added DispatchDomainEventsInterceptor for domain event dispatch on save
- Added IUser/CurrentUser abstraction for user context

Application Layer:
- Added PerformanceBehaviour for slow request warnings
- Added UnhandledExceptionBehaviour for centralized exception logging

Web API:
- Added Entity1Endpoints minimal API alternative to controllers
- Added EndpointGroupBase infrastructure for endpoint organization

Testing:
- Added TestcontainersWebApplicationFactory for realistic integration tests
- Added MSW (Mock Service Worker) for React API mocking tests

UI Improvements:
- Migrated to Tailwind CSS v4 with dark mode support
- Added Headless UI modals and Heroicons
- Consolidated Add/Edit forms into unified Entity1Form component
        </releaseNotes>
